note.quote:
Author of a supplement (covering Cant. 6:12 to the end;
                    probably originally in Greek), preserved at the end of the Syriac translation of
                    Gregory of Nyssa’s unfinished ‘Commentary on the Song of Songs’.

Also known as John of Beth Ruphina and John of Maiuma. An
                    anti-Chalcedonian presbyter, monk, and hagiographer of the 5th and 6th cent.;
                    dates of birth and death unknown.

Jewish Italian physician; biblical scholar and polymath;
                    author of a treatise about the usefulness of the Peshitta for the evaluation of
                    the Vulgate of the NT.

Author of a treatise on family and hereditary law;
                    metropolitan bp. Shemʿon wrote his law book in Persian, but it is known to us
                    only in the Syr. translation of an anonymous monk from Beth Qaṭraye.
